30/06/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- During a speech to a conference in Ohrid Wednesday (29 June), Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska called on Wednesday (29 June) for more co-ordination among institutions and firm action against corruption. 
Commenting on recent quarrels between the State Commission for the Fight Against Corruption and the Public Prosecutor's Office, Sekerinska stressed that instead of exchanging accusations, the two institutions should intensify collaboration. 
(Makfax, A1 TV - 29/06/05)
